OnePlus has revealed the launch date of its upcoming flagship smartphone, the OnePlus 6. The smartphone is set to be unveiled on 16 May 2018 at a launch event in London. Invitations to the event are open to the public and can be purchased from the OnePlus website for $21 – an early-bird price which will rise to $41 from Friday. The event will feature the launch of the new OnePlus smartphone, in addition to a demo area where attendees can try out the new device. “Witness the unveiling of the OnePlus 6 at the Copper Box Arena in London. Join Carl and other key members of OnePlus, along with some of the biggest names in tech, at our largest event ever,” it said.